# 🔐 CodeAlpha - Basic Network Sniffer

## 📌 Project Overview

This project was developed as part of the **CodeAlpha Cyber Security Internship**.

The **Basic Network Sniffer** is a Python application that captures and analyzes network packets using the Scapy library. It displays important packet information such as the source IP address, destination IP address, protocol, and packet length to help users understand how network communication works.

> **Note:** This project is intended for educational purposes and should only be used on networks you own or have permission to monitor.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

- Learn packet capturing techniques.
- Understand network protocols.
- Analyze packet information.
- Gain practical experience with Python and Scapy.

---

## ✨ Features

- Capture live network packets
- Display Source IP Address
- Display Destination IP Address
- Identify Protocol (TCP, UDP, ICMP)
- Show Packet Size
- Simple command-line interface
- Beginner-friendly

